  "prompt": "What causes a pulsating feeling under the left rib cage?",
  "response": "A pulsating feeling under the left rib cage can be caused by a variety of factors, ranging from benign to more serious conditions. It's important to consider the context of the sensation, including any accompanying symptoms, your overall health, and recent activities. Here are some possible causes:\n\n### 1. **Heart-Related Causes**\n- **Palpitations:** You might feel your heartbeat more prominently due to stress, anxiety, caffeine intake, or hormonal changes.\n- **Arrhythmias:** Irregular heartbeats can sometimes be felt in the chest area, including under the ribs.\n- **Enlarged Heart:** Conditions that cause the heart to enlarge can make its pulsations more noticeable.\n\n### 2. **Aortic Pulsation**\n- **Abdominal Aorta:** In some individuals, especially those who are thin, the abdominal aorta (a major blood vessel) can be felt pulsating beneath the left rib cage. This is usually normal unless accompanied by other symptoms.\n\n### 3. **Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm (AAA)**\n- **AAA:** This is a serious condition where the aorta becomes enlarged and can pulsate abnormally. Symptoms may include a deep, continuous pain in the abdomen or back, dizziness, or a feeling of fullness. If you suspect an AAA, seek medical attention immediately.\n\n### 4. **Gastrointestinal Causes**\n- **Gas and Bloating:** Excess gas can create sensations that might be interpreted as pulsating.\n- **Peristalsis:** The movement of the intestines can sometimes be felt, especially if you're hungry or have an active digestive system.\n\n### 5. **Musculoskeletal Factors**\n- **Muscle Twitches or Spasms:** Muscles under the rib cage can twitch, creating a pulsating sensation.\n- **Costochondritis:** Inflammation of the cartilage connecting the ribs to the breastbone can cause discomfort and unusual sensations.\n\n### 6. **Vascular Conditions**\n- **Splenic Artery Issues:** Conditions affecting arteries near the spleen can cause pulsating feelings.\n- **Vascular Shunts:** Abnormal connections between blood vessels might lead to unusual pulsations.\n\n### 7. **Other Factors**\n- **Body Position:** Certain positions can make normal bodily pulsations more noticeable.\n- **Physical Activity:** Recent or intense exercise can increase heart rate and blood flow, making pulsations more palpable.\n\n### When to Seek Medical Attention\n\nWhile some causes of a pulsating feeling under the left rib cage are harmless, others may require medical evaluation, especially if accompanied by:\n\n- Chest pain or discomfort\n- Shortness of breath\n- Dizziness or fainting\n- Sudden or severe abdominal pain\n- Rapid or irregular heartbeats\n\n### Recommendations\n\nIf you're experiencing a persistent or concerning pulsating sensation under your left rib cage, it's advisable to consult a healthcare professional. They can perform a thorough evaluation, which may include a physical examination, imaging studies, or other diagnostic tests to determine the underlying cause and appropriate treatment.\n\n**Note:** This information is intended for educational purposes and should not replace professional medical advice. Always seek the guidance of a qualified healthcare provider with any questions or concerns you may have regarding your health.",
